## 🧠 4. HTTPS C2 Communication

### Why attackers use HTTPS
- Encrypted → harder to inspect    ( C2 means server/system contrld by an attacker to commnct with infctd machines)
- Blends with normal traffic
- Bypasses basic detection

### Indicators
- Repeated HTTPS connections (e.g., every 60s)
- Unknown IP/domain
- Same destination consistently


