## 🧠 6. EDR Investigation (Critical)

### First Step
- Check **process tree**

### Suspicious Examples
- acrobat.exe → powershell.exe
- winword.exe → cmd.exe

### Also Check
- Command-line arguments
- Network connections
- Persistence (registry, scheduled tasks)


---

## 🧠 7. No DNS = Suspicious

### Why?
- Normal systems resolve domains first
- Direct IP connection may indicate evasion

### Possible Techniques
- Hardcoded IP in malware
- DNS bypass to avoid logging


---

## 🧠 8. Detection Thinking (SIEM)

### Example Detection Rules
- DNS queries > 50 per minute per host
- Same IP contacted every 60 seconds
- Direct IP HTTPS traffic (no DNS logs)

### Tools
- SIEM (e.g., Splunk)


